  "articleSummary": "This tutorial uses animated timeline diagrams to visualize the asynchronous execution flow of JavaScript Promises, clarifying exactly when callbacks are evaluated. It addresses a frequent developer mistake—passing an immediately invoked function to `.then()` instead of a function reference—and demonstrates correct patterns through four progressive examples, including concurrent execution and `Promise.all`. Targeted at intermediate JavaScript developers, the piece employs a straightforward, educational tone to reinforce accurate mental models of non-blocking code. By consistently framing promise resolution as a chronological timeline, the article provides a reusable visual metaphor that aids in debugging and understanding async workflows.",
